// v1.3 forward (v2-updated): strict mode rejects a spread whose
// source's static type is genuinely unknown. Pre-v2 this fixture
// used `1 + 2` as the source; v2 splits that case off into the
// cross-mode `NonSpreadableSource` because the type is statically
// known to be non-dict. An untyped closure parameter leaks `Any`
// into the body scope, so the inner spread's source has no static
// type — strict demands a `<T>` hint.
// EXPECTED: 1 × SpreadSourceTypeUnknown (plus closure-param
// diagnostics for the untyped `n`).
#strict
{ f: (n) => { ...n } }
